    "recap_headline": "North Carolina State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TALLAHASSEE, Fla. \u2013\nNo. 11 Florida State used a six-run sixth inning to pull away from No. 10 NC State and won 11-5 Saturday afternoon at Mike Martin Field at Dick Howser Stadium.\nThe first four innings were a back-and-forth battle, with the game tied at four going into the fifth. Seminole first baseman Myles Bailey hit two home runs, with his second putting the Seminoles ahead 5-4, a lead they maintained.\nThe Wolfpack (18-5, 3-2) took the lead in the fourth with three runs after one of four Seminole errors allowed a run to score with the bases loaded, followed by\nLuke Nixon\nsingling in two runs to make it 4-3. Nixon finished with four hits in five at-bats and a run scored.\nTy Head\nhit his eighth home run of the season to give the Pack a run in the top of the eighth.\nJacob Dudan\n(4-1) suffered his first loss of the season after pitching five innings, allowing eight runs on eight hits with four walks and six strikeouts.\nCollins Black\nrelieved him, striking out two but allowing three runs on four hits.\nDanny Heintz\ncalmed the game with 2.1 scoreless innings, walking two and striking out two.\nFSU starter Trey Beard pitched only 3.2 innings as the Pack scored four runs on six hits, walking four and striking out seven. Chris Knier (1-0) entered after Beard and earned the win.\nNC State had opportunities, going 2-14 with runners in scoring position and 0-6 with runners on third and less than two outs.\nAfter the Seminoles scored two in the first, NC State's\nRett Johnson\ncontinued to produce, knocking an infield single to bring in Nixon. Johnson is now hitting .439 to lead the Pack and has 19 RBIs.\nFlorida State added another run in the second after back-to-back doubles; however, as they have throughout the series, the Wolfpack responded with a three-run fourth.\nThe big hit came from Florida State's Brayden Dowd, who hit a grand slam in the bottom of the sixth off Black.\nThe series wraps up tomorrow, Sunday, March 22nd, at 1 p.m., as the Wolfpack aims for its second ACC series win of the season.",
